 to be Ready and accessible via HTTPS on port 9200 through a Service named `es-http`\\n\\nI'll need to create a ConfigMap for the Elasticsearch configuration with TLS and security settings, a headless Service for inter-node discovery, an `es-http` Service for external HTTPS access, and a StatefulSet with 3 replicas running the Elasticsearch container.\\n\\nFor TLS, I'll use the `es-http-tls` secret for both HTTP client connections and inter-node transport communication since that's what's available. The configuration will enable xpack security and set up both layers to use the certificate and CA from that secret.\\n\\nWriting Elasticsearch configuration... Setting up the StatefulSet with init containers to configure system limits, mounting the TLS certificates and config files, and injecting the elastic user password through environment variables from a secret. Configuring the discovery settings with the fully qualified domain names for each pod in the StatefulSet, and setting the initial master nodes to bootstrap the cluster. I need to write out the complete YAML configuration and apply it, though I should first verify what's already in place and consider how to handle transport TLS across the nodes.\\n\\nWriting Elasticsearch config...\\n\\nI'm realizing that `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is only needed for the initial bootstrap, so I should remove it once the cluster is running to avoid issues with node restarts.\\n\\nFor a StatefulSet, the node names will be `elasticsearch-0`, `elasticsearch-1`, `elasticsearch-2` based on the hostname pattern, so I need to make sure those match exactly if I do use that setting.\\n\\nLet me put together the full deployment YAML now, and I should also check what's already in the stage directory to see if there are any existing configs or scripts I need to account for.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"stop_details\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":11683,\"cache